        <QuestionText>Case No 3:

NGO XXX engaged in improving the status of women in rural Rajasthan, has signed a contract with the Women and Child Development Department of the state government to improve the declining sex ratio in the district of Nagaur. The contract involves surveying the installed sonography machines and monitoring the incidents of medical termination of pregnancy cases conducted by health professionals including doctors, nurses, trained/untrained traditional dais in the district. 

The NGO XXX is partly funded by an Indian public trust and partly by the state government Health Department. As a program officer assigned to carry out this activity, you have to enlist the programmatic and administrative support of the District Health Officer (DHO). Unless the instruction is given by the Health Secretary at the state government level, the DHO will not extend her/his co-operation. Prepare a letter giving outline of the exact areas of co-operation you require from the DHO and request the Health Secretary to do the needful. The letter may contain the following points:

i)	Brief status report about the incidents of female foeticide in the district
ii)	Brief reference to public health authorities responsible for implementing the provisions of the Medical Termination of Pregnancy Act (MTP Act) at the district level
iii)	Brief details about the contract between your NGO and the state Women and Child Development 
iv)	Brief details of the nature of co-operation expected from the DHO during the duration of the activity



</QuestionText>
