        <QuestionText>Case no 2:

NGO ABCD located in a small municipal town in eastern Uttar Pradesh engaged in improving school enrollment of urban poor children under the Right To Education Act has agreed to build capacities of members of School Management Committees of 15 Municipal elementary schools in the town. 

The NGO ABCD is funded entirely by a public sector company as part of their Corporate Social Responsibility (CSR). As a Board Member of the organization, you have to place a proposal for undertaking the above activity in front of a committee consisting of the Chief Managing Director, the General Manager (Finance) and the General Manager (Human Resources) of the company to get the budget approved.  

a)	Please prepare an introduction justifying the need for undertaking the activity and how it will add value to the company’s CSR rating. Your introduction should be prepared along the following points:
i)	Brief data about status of school education in the municipal schools (please refer to latest Annual Status of Education Report (ASER) in your town
ii)	Brief reference to the provisions under the Right To Education Act
iii)	Brief reference to the criteria used to rate/assess the CSR engagement of public sector companies and how this activity will increase the CSR rating of the company 
b)	As a Board Member of the NGO ABC, describe the preparations that will be required for the effective implementation of this activity
